BEAUJOLAIS—1966 VINTAGE

The best for present drinking. Beaujolais like the 1967 above has a life that is counted in months rather than years. However, the great townships of Beaujolais such as Moulin-a-Vent and Fleurie require more bottle age to reach their peak. We list some oustanding examples below from Brouilly, Chiroubles, Morgon, Chenas, Fleurie and Moulin-a-Vent. They are the prime examples from this popular wine-growing area.

Among the best we have ever tasted are those of the Rt. Hon. Ernest Marples, who has earned special admiration not only for his wine but as a Member of the British Cabinet and as its Minister of Transport.

His wines are listed below. They represent the best of their class.
